\title{Hausdorff space}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-12}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{Munkres [[munkres-2000-topology]] Section 17}
\MML{pre_topsc}{def 10}{V8}

\p{Let #{(X,\mathcal{T})} be a [[gt-0002]]. We say #{X} is \define{Hausdorff} if for any two distinct points #{x,y\in X}, there are disjoint open sets #{U,V\subset X} such that #{x\in U} and #{y\in V}.}

\rmk{The literature also calls this the \define{#{T_{2}} Property}.}
